I think the problem is in this line:

dataset = tf.data.Dataset.from_generator(generator,tf.float32)

To match the signature of generator(), which returns a pair of objects, the output_types argument should be a pair of types, rather than a single type tf.float32. For example, changing that line as follows makes your code work for me:

dataset = tf.data.Dataset.from_generator(generator, (tf.float32, tf.float32))

body:
I think the problem is in this line:

```python
dataset = tf.data.Dataset.from_generator(generator,tf.float32)
```

To match the signature of `generator()`, which returns a pair of objects, the `output_types` argument should be a pair of types, rather than a single type `tf.float32`. For example, changing that line as follows makes your code work for me:

```python
dataset = tf.data.Dataset.from_generator(generator, (tf.float32, tf.float32))
```
